  "prompt": "What are the lyrics to the Korean happy birthday song?",
  "response": "The Korean version of the Happy Birthday song, known as \"\uc0dd\uc77c \ucd95\ud558\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4\" (Saeng-il Chukha Hamnida), has simple and easy-to-remember lyrics. Here they are:\n\n\uc0dd\uc77c \ucd95\ud558\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4  \n\uc0dd\uc77c \ucd95\ud558\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4  \n\uc0ac\ub791\ud558\ub294 [\uc774\ub984] (or [\uce5c\uad6c])  \n\uc0dd\uc77c \ucd95\ud558\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4  \n\nTranslated to English, it means:\n\nHappy Birthday to you  \nHappy Birthday to you  \nDear [Name] (or [Friend])  \nHappy Birthday to you  \n\nYou can replace [\uc774\ub984] (name) or [\uce5c\uad6c] (friend) with the person's name or a term of endearment. It\u2019s a straightforward and heartfelt way to celebrate someone\u2019s birthday in Korean!",
